  "script": "export const meta = { name: 'camiel-tech-debt', description: 'Implement tech debt items for Project-Camiel', phases: [{ title: 'Tech debt' }] };\n\nconst P = '/Volumes/T9/Code/projects/Project-Camiel';\n\nphase('Tech debt');\n\nconst r = await agent('Implement tech debt items for Project-Camiel (Godot 4) at ' + P + '. Read project.godot, export_presets.cfg, scripts/tools/quality_gate.py, docs/build-and-release.md first. Then create ALL of the following files with FULL correct content:\\n\\n1. Create .github/workflows/export.yml with this EXACT content:\\nname: Export\\non:\\n  push:\\n    branches: [main]\\n  pull_request:\\n  tags:\\n    - \"v*\"\\njobs:\\n  export:\\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\\n    steps:\\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\\n      - uses: gobject/godot-action@v3\\n        with:\\n          godot-version: 4.6.2\\n      - name: Quality Gate\\n        run: godot --headless --path . --script res://scripts/tools/verify_camiel_resources.gd\\n      - name: Export Windows\\n        run: |\\n          mkdir -p builds/$GITHUB_REF_NAME/windows\\n          godot --headless --path . --export-release \"Windows Desktop\" builds/$GITHUB_REF_NAME/windows/Camiel.exe\\n      - name: Package\\n        run: cd builds/$GITHUB_REF_NAME/windows && zip -r Camiel-windows.zip Camiel.exe\\n      - uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\\n        with:\\n          name: camiel-windows-$GITHUB_REF_NAME\\n          path: builds/$GITHUB_REF_NAME/windows/\\n      - name: Create Release\\n        if: startsWith(github.ref, refs/tags/)\\n        uses: softprops/action-gh-release@v1\\n        with:\\n          files: builds/$GITHUB_REF_NAME/windows/*\\n        env:\\n          GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\\n\\n2. Create docs/code-signing.md with FULL educator-style content covering: what code signing is, Windows SmartScreen, free option SignPath.io, paid options Digicert/SSL.com, env vars AUTHENTICODE_CERT_PATH + AUTHENTICODE_PASSWORD, GitHub Actions signtool step (shows it is SKIPPED if cert absent), local signtool command, self-signed for dev only, and a clear DO NOT commit certs warning.\\n\\n3. Create scripts/title_screen.gd: extends Node2D, @onready play_button, @onready camiel_sprite. _ready: play_button.grab_focus(), play idle animation. _input: Enter key. _on_play_pressed: change_scene_to_file(main_menu.tscn). version_text = alpha-v0.0.3.\\n\\n4. Create scenes/title_screen.tscn: Node2D (script title_screen.gd), ColorRect fullscreen bg, VBoxContainer centered, Label \"Camiel\", Button \"Play!\" connected to _on_play_pressed, Button \"About\", Label \"alpha-v0.0.3\" bottom-right.\\n\\n5. Create scripts/ui/version_label.gd: extends Label, _ready sets text = \"Camiel alpha-v0.0.3\".\\n\\n6. Create scenes/ui/version_label.tscn: Label with anchors preset 3 (bottom-right), text \"Camiel alpha-v0.0.3\", horizontal_alignment = 2 (right).\\n\\n7. Update project.godot: set main scene to res://scenes/title_screen.tscn, add [autoload] Accessibility=res://scripts/accessibility.gd.\\n\\n8. Create .gitattributes with: * text=auto, *.exe binary, *.dll binary, *.zip binary.\\n\\n9. Update docs/build-and-release.md: add section \"CI/CD Pipeline\" explaining the GitHub Actions workflow, quality gate step, export step, artifact upload, and release creation on tags.\\n\\nReturn FULL contents of all new/modified files.', { label: 'tech-debt', tier: 'medium', cwd: P });\n\nreturn { ok: true, result: r };",
